  "instructions": [
    "cut the cassaba squash in half lengthwise and scoop out the seeds.",
    "place the squash in a large ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "add the yuzu juice, honey, clarified butter, cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, crushed red pepper, and salt to the tagine.",
    "bring the mixture to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 30 minutes.",
    "remove the squash from the heat and stir in the parsley, garlic, and lemon juice.",
    "return the tagine to the heat and cook for an additional 10 minutes, or until the squash is tender.",
    "season the tagine with additional salt to taste.",
    "serve the cassaba tagine hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired"
